OL,3,CJury told not to speculate on absence
OL,4,Cof Rochdale grooming trial defendant
OL,6,FIn his closing speech to the jury on
OL,7,FMonday 12 May, his barrister Shahnawaz
OL,8,FKhan said it was his client's case
OL,9,Fthat Bashir had consensual sex with
OL,10,FGirl B on a sole occasion but was not
OL,11,Finvolved with any sexual activity at
OL,12,Fthe address in Chadderton.
OL,14,FMr Khan reminded the jury of the "very
OL,15,Fcomprehensive" directions previously
OL,16,Fgiven to them by Judge Jonathan Seely.
OL,18,FMr Khan said: "You are not to
OL,19,Fspeculate why Mr Bashir is not here.
